>{{cite web | url=https://www.nw.de/sport/lokalsport/kreis_herford/herford/22102348_Herforder-Ice-Dragons-feiern-den-groessten-Triumph-der-Vereinsgeschichte.html | title=Herforder Ice Dragons feiern den gr\u00f6\u00dften Triumph der Vereinsgeschichte | publisher=www.nw.de | first=Markus | last=Voss | date=3 April 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Herford Ice Dragons celebrate the greatest triumph in club history}}</ref> [[DEL]] team, [[Krefeld EV]] applied for a licence for their U23 team to compete in Oberliga North, this was accepted.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://rp-online.de/sport/eishockey/kev/krefeld-der-kev-81-kehrt-in-die-oberliga-zurueck_aid-36605013 | title=Der KEV\u201981 kehrt in die Oberliga zur\u00fcck | publisher=[[Rheinische Post]] | first=H | last=Schoofs | date=6 February 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=The KEV\u201981 returns to the top division}}</ref> [[EC Harzer Falken]] withdrew from the league after beginning insolvency proceedings.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.harzer-falken.de/news/artikel/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=613&cHash=b3911b13445d124f75c3dc0b776755c7 | title=Harzer Falken planen f\u00fcr die Regionalliga Nord | publisher=Harzer Falken | first= | last= | date=17 April 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Harzer Falken plan for the Regionalliga Nord}}</ref> [[ECC Preussen Berlin]] had the chance to apply for a licence, even though they were relegated from the previous season but they could not meet the conditions so remained in Regionlliga Ost.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.hockeyweb.de/oberliga/nord/ecc-preussen-berlin-zieht-sich-in-die-regionalliga-zurueck-97962 | title=ECC Preussen Berlin zieht sich in die Regionalliga zur\u00fcck | publisher=www.hockeyweb.de | first=Friedhelm | last=Thelen | date=12 July 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=ECC Preussen Berlin withdraws to the Regionalliga}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#feb634;\" colspan=\"7\"| <span style=\"color:black;\">Oberliga South Teams: 2019\u201320 Season</span>\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Team\n! colspan=2|Location\n! rowspan=2|Arena\n! rowspan=2|Capacity\n! rowspan=2|Founded\n! rowspan=2|Joined <br> league\n|-\n! City !! State\n|-\n| [[EV F\u00fcssen]] || [[F\u00fcssen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Bundesleistungszentrum Kienbaum|Bundesleistungszentrum]] || align=center|4,700 || align=center|1922 || align=center|2019\n|-\n| [[H\u00f6chstadter EC]] || [[H\u00f6chstadt]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion H\u00f6chstadt || align=center|2,000 || align=center|1993 || align=center|2018\n|-\n| [[ECDC Memmingen]] || [[Memmingen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissportstadion am H\u00fchnerberg || align=center|3,850 || align=center|1992 || align=center|2017\n|-\n| [[EV Lindau Islanders]] || [[Lindau]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eichwaldstadion || align=center|1,100 || align=center|1976 || align=center|2016\n|-\n| [[EC Peiting]] || [[Peiting]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion Peiting || align=center|2,500 || align=center|1973 || align=center|2000\n|-\n| [[SC Riessersee]] || [[Garmisch-Partenkirchen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Olympia-Eissport-Zentrum]] || align=center|6,926 || align=center|1920 || align=center|2018\n|-\n| [[ERC Sonthofen 1999]] || [[Sonthofen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissporthalle Sonthofen || align=center|2,860 || align=center|1999 || align=center|2014\n|-\n| [[EV Regensburg|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg]] || [[Regensburg]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Donau Arena]] || align=center|4,961 || align=center|1962 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Starbulls Rosenheim]]  || [[Rosenheim]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Emilo Stadion || align=center|4,750 || align=center|2000 || align=center|2017\n|-\n| [[Selber W\u00f6lfe]] || [[Selb]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Hutschenreuther Eissporthalle || align=center|4,082 || align=center|2004 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[1. EV Weiden]] || [[Weiden in der Oberpfalz|Weiden]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion Weiden || align=center|2,560 || align=center|1985 || align=center|2012\n|-\n| [[Deggendorfer SC]] || [[Deggendorf]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissporthalle an der Trat || align=center|4,000 || align=center|2002 || align=center|2019\n|}\n\n[[Deggendorf SC]] joined Oberliga South for 2019/20 after being relegated from [[DEL2]]. [[EV Landshut]] left the league after being promoted to DEL2. [[EV F\u00fcssen]] joined the league from the [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Bayernliga]] while [[EHC Waldkraiburg]] went the other direction. The champions of Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest, SC Bietigheim-Bissingen were not eligible for promotion to Oberliga South due to their first team playing in DEL2 ([[Bietigheim Steelers]]) \n\n==Oberliga North==\n\nOberliga North ran from 21 September 2019 till 10 March 2020. The league operated with a 44 match (4 matches against each team) regular season. The top six teams automatically qualified for the championship & promotion playoffs. The next four teams advanced to the qualification playoffs for two spots in the championship playoffs. The team finishing eleventh, had their season end after the regular season while the team that finished twelfth, was relegated to the [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Regionalliga]]. [[Tilburg Trappers]] topped the league standings at the end of the regular season, being crowned Oberliga North premiers.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://tilburg.com/nieuws/tilburg-trappers-als-oberliga-nord-meister-de-play-offs-in/ | title=Tilburg Trappers als Oberliga Nord Meister de play-offs in | publisher=www.tilburg.com | first= | last= | date=2 March 2020 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=Dutch | trans-title=Tilburg Trappers enter the play-offs as Oberliga Nord Meister}}</ref> [[Krefeld EV|Krefeld EV U23's]] finished last and would have been relegated until the league decided to suspend all promotion and relegation for the season due to [[COVID-19]] ending the season early.<ref name=\"DEBEARLYEND\"/>\n\n===Regular season===\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WL OT\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://www.eliteprospects.com/league/germany3/2019-2020 www.eliteprospects.com]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=TT |team2=HE |team3=HC |team4=HI |team5=IL |team6=HS |team7=SB |team8=FD |team9=RP |team10=ME |team11=ED |team12=KE\n\n<!--Update team results here and then (if needed) positions above. Don't forget to update the date.-->\n|win_TT= 31 |OTwin_TT= 6  |OTloss_TT= 1 |loss_TT= 6  |gf_TT= 209 |ga_TT= 116 <!-- Tilburg Trappers -->\t\n|win_HE= 31 |OTwin_HE= 1  |OTloss_HE= 2 |loss_HE= 10 |gf_HE= 198 |ga_HE= 141 <!-- Herner EV 2007 -->\n|win_HC= 25 |OTwin_HC= 2  |OTloss_HC= 5 |loss_HC= 12 |gf_HC= 184 |ga_HC= 122 <!-- Hamburg Crocodiles -->\n|win_HI= 21 |OTwin_HI= 4  |OTloss_HI= 7 |loss_HI= 12 |gf_HI= 140 |ga_HI= 117 <!-- Hannover Indians -->\n|win_IL= 22 |OTwin_IL= 3  |OTloss_IL= 3 |loss_IL= 16 |gf_IL= 168 |ga_IL= 134 <!-- Icefighters Leipzig -->\n|win_HS= 20 |OTwin_HS= 5  |OTloss_HS= 2 |loss_HS= 17 |gf_HS= 174 |ga_HS= 153 <!-- Hannover Scorpions -->\n|win_SB= 19 |OTwin_SB= 4  |OTloss_SB= 3 |loss_SB= 18 |gf_SB= 168 |ga_SB= 154 <!-- Saale Bulls Halle -->\n|win_FD= 17 |OTwin_FD= 3  |OTloss_FD= 3 |loss_FD= 21 |gf_FD= 151 |ga_FD= 161 <!-- F\u00fcchse Duisburg -->\n|win_RP= 13 |OTwin_RP= 4  |OTloss_RP= 6 |loss_RP= 21 |gf_RP= 133 |ga_RP= 167 <!-- Rostock Piranhas -->\n|win_ME= 10 |OTwin_ME= 3  |OTloss_ME= 4 |loss_ME= 27 |gf_ME= 137 |ga_ME= 202 <!-- Moskitos Essen -->\n|win_ED= 9  |OTwin_ED= 3  |OTloss_ED= 2 |loss_ED= 30 |gf_ED= 117 |ga_ED= 189 <!-- Erfurt Black Dragons -->\n|win_KE= 7  |OTwin_KE= 1  |OTloss_KE= 1 |loss_KE= 35 |gf_KE= 119 |ga_KE= 242 <!-- Krefelder EV U23 -->\n\n<!--Status-->\n<!--|status_TEAM=C-->\n<!--|status_TEAM=P-->\n<!--|status_TEAM=R-->\n\n<!--Team definitions (wikilinks in table)-->\n|name_TT=[[Tilburg Trappers]]\n|name_HE=Herner EV 2007\n|name_HC=[[Hamburg Crocodiles]]\n|name_HI=[[Hannover Indians]]\n|name_IL=[[Blue Lions Leipzig|Icefighters Leipzig]]\n|name_HS=[[Hannover Scorpions]]\n|name_SB=[[Saale Bulls Halle]]\n|name_FD=[[F\u00fcchse Duisburg]]\n|name_RP=[[Rostock Piranhas]]\n|name_ME=[[ESC Moskitos Essen]]\n|name_ED=Erfurt Black Dragons\n|name_KE=[[Krefelder EV|Krefelder EV U23]]\n\n<!--Qualification and relegation column definitions-->\n|res_col_header=QR\n|col_CP=green1|text_CP=[[2019\u201320 Oberliga (ice hockey) season#Championship playoffs|Oberliga <br> Championship playoffs]]\n|col_QP=blue1|text_QP=[[2019\u201320 Oberliga (ice hockey) season#Qualification playoffs|Nord <br> Qualification playoffs]]\n|col_REL=red1|text_REL=[[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Regionalliga]]\n\n<!--Update team qualifications here (defined below)-->\n|result1=CP|result2=CP|result3=CP|result4=CP|result5=CP|result6=CP\n|result7=QP|result8=QP|result9=QP|result10=QP\n|result12=REL\n\n<!--Table settings and rules-->\n|class_rules= <br> ''Tie-break:'' 1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored <br> ''Points:'' 3 points for regulation win; 2 points for OT or SO win; 1 point for OT or SO loss; 0 points for regulation loss\n}}\n\n===Qualification playoffs===\n\nTeams finishing seventh to tenth play best of three match series in the qualification playoffs to determine the final two places from Oberliga North in the Championship playoffs. The matches occurred between 6 March and 10 March 2020.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| bgcolor=\"#BBF3BB\" |<small>[[2019\u201320 Oberliga (ice hockey) season#Championship playoffs|Qualified for Championship playoffs]]</small>\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n! width=\"200px\" |Team 1\n! width=\"200px\" |Team 2\n! width=\"120px\" |Series result\n! width=\"80px\"  |Match 1\n! width=\"80px\"  |Match 2\n! width=\"80px\"  |Match 3\n|-\n| bgcolor=\"#BBF3BB\"|[[Saale Bulls Halle]] || [[ESC Moskitos Essen]] || 2:0 || [https://www.gamepitch.de/deb/oberliga/oberliga-playoffs/gamereport/?gameId=074ab78e-0c59-4afa-a635-deb76c47c7fa&divisionId=deboln_prepl 7\u20132] || [https://www.gamepitch.de/deb/oberliga/oberliga-playoffs/gamereport/?gameId=9674556c-5009-4cea-bbd5-328900f31203&divisionId=6508 5\u20134] || \u2013\n|-\n| [[F\u00fcchse Duisburg]] || bgcolor=\"#BBF3BB\"|[[Rostock Piranhas]] || 1:2 || [https://www.gamepitch.de/deb/oberliga/oberliga-playoffs/gamereport/?gameId=bbbfeb1a-9882-45e8-841a-01afce510b16&divisionId=6508 3\u20132] || [https://www.gamepitch.de/deb/oberliga/oberliga-playoffs/gamereport/?gameId=957e4405-77c4-483f-9273-ab9d27526e13&divisionId=6508 3\u20134] || [https://www.gamepitch.de/deb/oberliga/oberliga-playoffs/gamereport/?gameId=fb851583-f185-4824-9b55-8519d224576b&divisionId=6508 2\u20133] <small>(OT)</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Oberliga South==\n\nOberliga South ran from 27 September 2019 till 8 March 2020. The league was broken into two stages. Stage one, the regular season, had all twelve teams compete in a home and away round before splitting into two regional groups for a second home and away round for a total of 32 matches. The top ten teams advanced to the Oberliga South qualification round to determine the league premier and eight qualifiers for the Oberliga championship playoffs. The bottom two teams advanced to the relegation playoffs with six [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Bayernliga]] teams. [[ECDC Memmingen|Memmingen Indians]] finished top of the regular season but [[EV Regensburg|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg]] topped the fifty match qualification round to claim the Oberliga South premiership.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mittelbayerische.de/sport-nachrichten/sagenhaft-die-eisbaeren-sind-meister-21510-art1889040.html | title=Sagenhaft: Die Eisb\u00e4ren sind Meister! | publisher=www.mittelbayerische.de | first=Claus-Dieter | last=Wotruba | date=8 March 2020 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Legendary: The polar bears are masters!}}</ref> [[ERC Sonthofen Bulls]] and [[H\u00f6chstadter EC]] finished in the bottom two, but the relegation playoffs were cancelled due to [[COVID-19]], so neither team was relegated on sporting performance.<ref name=\"DEBEARLYEND\"/> However, ERC Sonthofen declared [[bankruptcy]] and withdrew from the league, confirming their relegation next season.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.hockeyweb.de/oberliga/sued/erc-sonthofen-spielbetriebsgesellschaft-mbh-meldet-insolvenz-an-100690 | title=ERC Sonthofen Spielbetriebsgesellschaft mbH meldet Insolvenz an | publisher=www.hockeyweb.de | first= | last= | date=27 February 2020 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=ERC Sonthofen files for bankruptcy}}</ref>\n\n===Regular season===\n\n{|\n|- valign=top\n|\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#feb634;\" colspan=\"2\"| <span>Group A</span>\n|-\n!width=1%|#\n!width=85%|Team\n|-\n|align=left|1\n|align=left|[[EV F\u00fcssen]]\n|-\n|align=left|2\n|align=left|ECDC Memmingen\n|-\n|align=left|3\n|align=left|EV Lindau Islanders\n|-\n|align=left|4\n|align=left|[[EC Peiting]]\n|-\n|align=left|5\n|align=left|[[SC Riessersee]]\n|-\n|align=left|6\n|align=left|ERC Sonthofen Bulls\n|-\n|}\n|\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#feb634;\" colspan=\"2\"| <span>Group B</span>\n|-\n!width=1%|#\n!width=85%|Team\n|-\n|align=left|1\n|align=left|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg\n|-\n|align=left|2\n|align=left|[[Starbulls Rosenheim]]\n|-\n|align=left|3\n|align=left|Selber W\u00f6lfe\n|-\n|align=left|4\n|align=left|H\u00f6chstadter EC\n|-\n|align=left|5\n|align=left|1. EV Weiden\n|-\n|align=left|6\n|align=left|[[Deggendorfer SC]]\n|-\n|}\n|}\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WL OT\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://www.eliteprospects.com/league/germany3/2019-2020 www.eliteprospects.com]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team