bulls Rosenheim]]\n|-\n|align=left|6\n|align=left|[[EC Peiting]]\n|-\n|align=left|7\n|align=left|[[EV F\u00fcssen]]\n|-\n|align=left|8\n|align=left|Selber W\u00f6lfe\n|}\n|\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#feb634;\" colspan=\"2\"| <span>South</span>\n|-\n!width=1%|#\n!width=85%|Team\n|-\n|align=left|1\n|align=left|[[Tilburg Trappers]]\n|-\n|align=left|2\n|align=left|Herner EV 2007\n|-\n|align=left|3\n|align=left|[[Hamburg Crocodiles]]\n|-\n|align=left|4\n|align=left|[[Hannover Indians]]\n|-\n|align=left|5\n|align=left|[[Blue Lions Leipzig|Icefighters Leipzig]]\n|-\n|align=left|6\n|align=left|[[Hannover Scorpions]]\n|-\n|align=left|7\n|align=left|[[Saale Bulls Halle]]\n|-\n|align=left|8\n|align=left|[[Rostock Piranhas]]\n|}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Germany|Ice hockey}}\n* [http://www.esbg.de/ Official website]\n* [https://www.eliteprospects.com/league/germany3 Elite Prospects home]\n\n{{Oberliga (Ice Hockey)}}\n{{Oberliga (ice hockey) seasons}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oberliga (Ice Hockey) Season 2019-20}}\n[[Category:Oberliga (ice hockey) seasons]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 in German ice hockey]]\n[[Category:Sports events cancelled due to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|Oberliga]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox sports season\n| title            \t= 2019\u201320 Oberliga season\n| league          \t= [[Oberliga (ice hockey)|Oberliga]]\n| sport           \t= [[Ice Hockey]]\n| logo           \t= \n| pixels         \t= \n| caption      \t  \t=\n| color          \t= #c7bf98\n| color_text     \t= black\n| duration         \t= 28 September 2019 \u2013 11 March 2020\n| no_of_teams      \t= 24\n| no_of_games      \t= \n| attendance       \t= \n| TV               \t= Sprade TV <small>(select teams)</small>\n| season           \t= Regular season\n| season_champs    \t= [[Tilburg Trappers]] <small>(North)</small> <br> [[EV Regensburg|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg]] <small>(South)</small> \n| top_scorer       \t= Brad Snetsinger <small>(North)</small> <br> Ian McDonald <small>(South)</small>\n| top_scorer_link  \t= \n| promote               = N/A (no promotion playoffs <br> due to COVID-19)\n| promote_from          = <br>[[DEL2]]\n| relegate         \t= ERC Sonthofen Bulls <br> <small>(bankruptcy)</small>\n| relegate_to      \t= [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Regionalliga]]\n| finals           \t= Playoffs\n| finals_link      \t=\n| finals_champ     \t= No champion <br> <small>(Championship playoffs not contested)</small>\n| seasonslist      \t= Oberliga seasons\n| seasonslistnames \t= Oberliga\n| prevseason_link  \t= 2018\u201319 Oberliga (ice hockey) season\n| prevseason_year \t= 2018\u201319\n| nextseason_link  \t= 2020\u201321 Oberliga (ice hockey) season\n| nextseason_year  \t= 2020\u201321\n}}\n\nThe 2019/20 [[Oberliga (ice hockey)|Oberliga]] season was the 61st season of the Oberliga, the third-tier of [[Germany|German]] [[ice hockey]]. The Oberliga operated with two regional leagues, North and South. 24 teams competed in the season that spanned from 28 September 2019 till 11 March 2020. The regular season and championship playoff qualifyers was completed, but the season was then cut short due to the [[Coronavirus pandemic]] ([[COVID-19]]) and the remainder of the Oberliga season was cancelled by [[Deutscher Eishockey-Bund|DEB]].<ref name=\"DEBEARLYEND\">{{cite web | url=https://www.deb-online.de/2020/03/11/vorzeitiges-saisonende-aller-ligen-des-deb-spielbetriebs/ | title=Vorzeitiges Saisonende aller Ligen des DEB-Spielbetriebs | publisher=[[Deutscher Eishockey-Bund]] | first= | last= | date=11 March 2020 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Early season end to all DEB sanctioned leagues}}</ref> The championship playoffs were not contested so no Oberliga champion was named. There was also no sporting promotion or relegation, with ERC Sonthofen the only team to be relegated due to the club entering insolvency. [[Tilburg Trappers]] were crowned Oberliga North premiers, while [[EV Regensburg|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg]] were crowned Oberliga South premiers.\n\n==Teams==\n\n{{Location map+|Germany|width=400|float=right\n |alt=Oberliga (ice hockey)\n |caption=2019/20 German teams in Oberliga\n |places=\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.434406 |long= 6.762329 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = left |label=[[F\u00fcchse Duisburg|Duisburg]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 50.984768 |long= 11.029880 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = bottom |label=[[Black Dragons Erfurt|Erfurt]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.455643 |long= 7.011555 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = bottom |label=[[Moskitos Essen|Essen]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.482170 |long= 11.965800 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = left |label=[[Saale Bulls Halle|Halle]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 53.551086 |long= 9.993682 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = top |label=[[Hamburg Crocodiles|Hamburg]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 52.533333 |long= 9.716667 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = top |label=[[Hannover Indians|Indians]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 52.533333 |long= 9.716667 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = bottom |label=[[Hannover Scorpions|Scorpions]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.538521 |long= 7.219260 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = top |label=[[Herner EV 2007|Herne]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.331699 |long= 6.559350 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = bottom |label=[[Krefeld Pinguine|Krefeld]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 51.339695 |long= 12.373075 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = right |label=[[Blue Lions Leipzig|Leipzig]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 54.092442 |long= 12.099147 |mark = Blue pog.svg |label_size=80 |position = right |label=[[Rostock Piranhas|Rostock]]}}\n  {{Location map~|Germany|lat= 47.569649 |long= 10.700433 |