80 |position = right |label=[[Tilburg Trappers|Tilburg]]}}\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#699efe;\" colspan=\"7\"| <span style=\"color:black;\">Oberliga North Teams: 2019\u201320 Season</span>\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Team\n! colspan=2|Location\n! rowspan=2|Arena\n! rowspan=2|Capacity\n! rowspan=2|Founded\n! rowspan=2|Joined <br> league\n|-\n! City !! State\n|-\n| [[F\u00fcchse Duisburg]] || [[Duisburg]] || {{flagicon|North Rhine-Westphalia}} [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] || [[Scania Arena]] || align=center|4,800 || align=center|1971 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Black Dragons Erfurt]] || [[Erfurt]] || {{flagicon|Thuringia}} [[Thuringia]] || Kartoffelhalle Erfurt || align=center|1,200 || align=center|2010 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Moskitos Essen]] || [[Essen]] || {{flagicon|North Rhine-Westphalia}} [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] || Eissporthalle Essen-West || align=center|3,850 || align=center|1994 || align=center|2015\n|-\n| [[Saale Bulls Halle]] || [[Halle (Saale)]] || {{flagicon|Saxony-Anhalt}} [[Saxony-Anhalt]] || Eissporthalle Halle || align=center|2,200 || align=center|2004 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Hamburg Crocodiles]] || [[Hamburg]] || {{flagicon|Hamburg}} [[Hamburg]] || Eisland Farmsen || align=center|2,300 || align=center|1990 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Hannover Indians]] || [[Hannover]] || {{flagicon|Lower Saxony}} [[Lower Saxony]] || [[Eisstadion am Pferdeturm]] || align=center|4,608 || align=center|1948 || align=center|2013\n|-\n| [[Hannover Scorpions]] || [[Hannover]] || {{flagicon|Lower Saxony}} [[Lower Saxony]] || Eishalle Langenhagen || align=center|3,800 || align=center|1996 || align=center|2013\n|-\n| [[Herner EV 2007]] || [[Herne, North Rhine-Westphalia|Herne]] || {{flagicon|North Rhine-Westphalia}} [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] || Gysenberghalle || align=center|3,700 || align=center|2007 || align=center|2012\n|-\n| [[Krefeld Pinguine|Krefeld Pinguine U23]]  || [[Krefeld]] || {{flagicon|North Rhine-Westphalia}} [[North Rhine-Westphalia]] || [[K\u00f6nig Palast]] || align=center|9,000 || align=center|1995 || align=center|2011\n|-\n| [[Blue Lions Leipzig|IceFighters Leipzig]] || [[Leipzig]] || {{flagicon|Saxony}} [[Saxony]] || Kohlrabizirkus Eisarena || align=center|2,500 || align=center|2010 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Rostock Piranhas]] || [[Rostock]] || {{flagicon|Mecklenburg-Vorpommern}} [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]] || Eishalle Rostock || align=center|2,000 || align=center|1990 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Tilburg Trappers]] || [[Tilburg]] || {{flagicon|North Brabant}} [[North Brabant]] || IJssportcentrum Tilburg || align=center|2,500 || align=center|1938 || align=center|2015\n|}\n\nThree [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Regionalliga]] teams declined promotion to Oberliga North ([[ECW Sande]], [[Herford EV]] and [[Sch\u00f6nheider Wolves]]).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nwzonline.de/eishockey/sande-eishockey-regionalligist-ecw-sande-nach-der-meisterfeier-ist-vor-den-playoffs_a_50,3,3813213379.html | title=Nach der Meisterfeier ist vor den Playoffs | publisher=www.NWZonline.de | first=Henning | last=Busch | date=8 February 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Early season end to all DEB sanctioned leagues}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nw.de/sport/lokalsport/kreis_herford/herford/22102348_Herforder-Ice-Dragons-feiern-den-groessten-Triumph-der-Vereinsgeschichte.html | title=Herforder Ice Dragons feiern den gr\u00f6\u00dften Triumph der Vereinsgeschichte | publisher=www.nw.de | first=Markus | last=Voss | date=3 April 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Herford Ice Dragons celebrate the greatest triumph in club history}}</ref> [[DEL]] team, [[Krefeld EV]] applied for a licence for their U23 team to compete in Oberliga North, this was accepted.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://rp-online.de/sport/eishockey/kev/krefeld-der-kev-81-kehrt-in-die-oberliga-zurueck_aid-36605013 | title=Der KEV\u201981 kehrt in die Oberliga zur\u00fcck | publisher=[[Rheinische Post]] | first=H | last=Schoofs | date=6 February 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=The KEV\u201981 returns to the top division}}</ref> [[EC Harzer Falken]] withdrew from the league after beginning insolvency proceedings.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.harzer-falken.de/news/artikel/?tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=613&cHash=b3911b13445d124f75c3dc0b776755c7 | title=Harzer Falken planen f\u00fcr die Regionalliga Nord | publisher=Harzer Falken | first= | last= | date=17 April 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=Harzer Falken plan for the Regionalliga Nord}}</ref> [[ECC Preussen Berlin]] had the chance to apply for a licence, even though they were relegated from the previous season but they could not meet the conditions so remained in Regionlliga Ost.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.hockeyweb.de/oberliga/nord/ecc-preussen-berlin-zieht-sich-in-die-regionalliga-zurueck-97962 | title=ECC Preussen Berlin zieht sich in die Regionalliga zur\u00fcck | publisher=www.hockeyweb.de | first=Friedhelm | last=Thelen | date=12 July 2019 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=German | trans-title=ECC Preussen Berlin withdraws to the Regionalliga}}</ref> \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#feb634;\" colspan=\"7\"| <span style=\"color:black;\">Oberliga South Teams: 2019\u201320 Season</span>\n|-\n! rowspan=2|Team\n! colspan=2|Location\n! rowspan=2|Arena\n! rowspan=2|Capacity\n! rowspan=2|Founded\n! rowspan=2|Joined <br> league\n|-\n! City !! State\n|-\n| [[EV F\u00fcssen]] || [[F\u00fcssen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Bundesleistungszentrum Kienbaum|Bundesleistungszentrum]] || align=center|4,700 || align=center|1922 || align=center|2019\n|-\n| [[H\u00f6chstadter EC]] || [[H\u00f6chstadt]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion H\u00f6chstadt || align=center|2,000 || align=center|1993 || align=center|2018\n|-\n| [[ECDC Memmingen]] || [[Memmingen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissportstadion am H\u00fchnerberg || align=center|3,850 || align=center|1992 || align=center|2017\n|-\n| [[EV Lindau Islanders]] || [[Lindau]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eichwaldstadion || align=center|1,100 || align=center|1976 || align=center|2016\n|-\n| [[EC Peiting]] || [[Peiting]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion Peiting || align=center|2,500 || align=center|1973 || align=center|2000\n|-\n| [[SC Riessersee]] || [[Garmisch-Partenkirchen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Olympia-Eissport-Zentrum]] || align=center|6,926 || align=center|1920 || align=center|2018\n|-\n| [[ERC Sonthofen 1999]] || [[Sonthofen]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissporthalle Sonthofen || align=center|2,860 || align=center|1999 || align=center|2014\n|-\n| [[EV Regensburg|Eisb\u00e4ren Regensburg]] || [[Regensburg]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || [[Donau Arena]] || align=center|4,961 || align=center|1962 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[Starbulls Rosenheim]]  || [[Rosenheim]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Emilo Stadion || align=center|4,750 || align=center|2000 || align=center|2017\n|-\n| [[Selber W\u00f6lfe]] || [[Selb]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Hutschenreuther Eissporthalle || align=center|4,082 || align=center|2004 || align=center|2010\n|-\n| [[1. EV Weiden]] || [[Weiden in der Oberpfalz|Weiden]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eisstadion Weiden || align=center|2,560 || align=center|1985 || align=center|2012\n|-\n| [[Deggendorfer SC]] || [[Deggendorf]] || {{flagicon|Bavaria}} [[Bavaria]] || Eissporthalle an der Trat || align=center|4,000 || align=center|2002 || align=center|2019\n|}\n\n[[Deggendorf SC]] joined Oberliga South for 2019/20 after being relegated from [[DEL2]]. [[EV Landshut]] left the league after being promoted to DEL2. [[EV F\u00fcssen]] joined the league from the [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Bayernliga]] while [[EHC Waldkraiburg]] went the other direction. The champions of Regionalliga S\u00fcdwest, SC Bietigheim-Bissingen were not eligible for promotion to Oberliga South due to their first team playing in DEL2 ([[Bietigheim Steelers]]) \n\n==Oberliga North==\n\nOberliga North ran from 21 September 2019 till 10 March 2020. The league operated with a 44 match (4 matches against each team) regular season. The top six teams automatically qualified for the championship & promotion playoffs. The next four teams advanced to the qualification playoffs for two spots in the championship playoffs. The team finishing eleventh, had their season end after the regular season while the team that finished twelfth, was relegated to the [[Regionalliga (ice hockey)|Regionalliga]]. [[Tilburg Trappers]] topped the league standings at the end of the regular season, being crowned Oberliga North premiers.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://tilburg.com/nieuws/tilburg-trappers-als-oberliga-nord-meister-de-play-offs-in/ | title=Tilburg Trappers als Oberliga Nord Meister de play-offs in | publisher=www.tilburg.com | first= | last= | date=2 March 2020 | accessdate=12 April 2020 | language=Dutch | trans-title=Tilburg Trappers enter the play-offs as Oberliga Nord Meister}}</ref> [[Krefeld EV|Krefeld EV U23's]] finished last and would have been relegated until the league decided to suspend all promotion and relegation for the season due to [[COVID-19]] ending the season early.<ref name=\"DEBEARLYEND\"/>\n\n===Regular season===\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WL OT\n|update=complete\n|source=[https://www.eliteprospects.com/league/germany3/2019-2020 www.eliteprospects.com]\n\n<!--Update team positions here-->\n|team1=TT |team2=HE |team3=HC |team4=HI |team5=IL |team6=HS |team7=SB |team8=FD |team9=RP |team10=ME |team11=ED |team12=KE\n\n<!--Update team results here and then (if needed) positions above. Don't forget to update the date.-->\n|win_TT= 31 |OTwin_TT= 6  |OTloss_TT= 1 |loss_TT= 6  |gf_TT= 209 |ga_TT= 116 <!-- Tilburg Trappers -->\t\n|win_HE= 31 |OTwin_